calibration.json
this file is generated by the guis calibration tool. 
the fiducial marks are hardcoded to known positions and the mapping is derived using a least squares method. 
this gives us the projection matrix for the camera, which we can use to convert between pixel coordinates and world coordinates(which are in mm).

laser_mapping.json
this file is generated by the collect_sweep.py and analyze_sweep script which is run in the hardware control room. 
it maps the pixel coordinates of the laser spots to the actual positions of the fibers(in mm).
this is done by illuminating the fibers with a laser and then using the calibration matrix to convert the pixel coordinates of the laser spots to world coordinates.
These scripts can be found at: TBD

positioner_centers.json
This file contains the physical (mm) center coordinates for each positioner. 
Generated by the circle_center script in TBD. The data for this comes from moving the positioner around the perimeter of its fully extended range, marking down mm positions as we go using the guis camera view, and then feeding those into the circle_center script. circle center will create